\date{2026-03-10}
\date{2026-03-17}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\contributor{samueltoth}
\meta{external}{https://github.com/samtoth/agda-synthetic-categories/pull/63}
\title{Closure properties of localisations and more}
\tag{changelog}
\import{stt-macros}

\p{
We show a slew of closure properties of localisations. These closure properties will
help us construct [simplicial types](Synthetic.Categories.Simplicial) and
[synthetic categories](stt-????).
}

\p{
For [localisations](stt-005F)/[reflective subuniverses](fre-8763) we show
[closure under retracts](fre-ABCC), and [formation of pullbacks](fre-ABCD),
[fibres, equalisers, sequential limits, retract types, equivalence types](fre-ABCE),
[quasiidempotent maps, and universes of retracts](fre-ABCH). We also show that
[propositions are local at families of maps whose domains are inhabited](fre-0012).
}

\p{
While most of these results appear in \citek{CORS20}, closure under forming
[quasiidempotent maps](fre-9876) and the [universe of retracts](fre-1A1D) do not to
our knowledge appear in the literature, and are due to [[egbertrijke]]. We show that
the type of quasiidempotent maps
[can be presented as an iterated limit over function types on the underlying type](fre-9875),
and from pullback closure obtain that it is itself local. From closure under
formation of quasiidempotent maps we use the [splitting construction](fre-2113) of
[[michaelshulman]] \citek{shulman-idempotents-2017} to obtain that the universe of
retracts of a local type is also local.
}

\p{
For [nullifications](Modalities.Instances.Nullification) we additionally show that
[universes of null types at families of propositions are themselves null at that family of propositions](fre-0001),
following [Rijke](egbertrijke), [Shulman](michaelshulmant) and Spitters
\citet{Thm 3.11}{RSS2020}. We
[extend this result to subuniverses that are closed under mapping out of the given family of propositions](fre-0000).
As corollaries, we obtain that the universe of
[simplicial](Synthetic.Categories.Simplicial)/[disjunctive](Synthetic.Categories.Disjunctive)
types is itself simplicial/disjunctive, and that the type of
[precategories](Synthetic.Categories.Precategories) is simplicial.
}

\p{
In addition to the above we add
[biinvertible maps](Foundations.BiinvertibleMap),
[surjections](Core.Surjection), [the canonical image](fre-2145)
and some basic properties of images, the
[6-for-2 property of equivalences](Foundations.6for2), and [small types](Core.Small).
We formalise that [small types are closed under retracts](fre-2140)
\citet{Thm 2.13}{de-jong-escardo-2023} using the [splitting construction](fre-2113),
that [universes of retracts of a type are small](fre-2352). Small types are a
natural setting in which to consider [type theoretic replacement](fre-2143), so we
register that too building on [[samueltoth]]'s formalisation of
[the modified join construction](stt-008G).
}

\p{
We also show that
[maps whose action on identifications have a section are embeddings](fre-0012),
that [retracts are closed under taking actions on identifications](fre-2138), and
that maps #{f : A \to B} whose
[precomposition map #{A^f} have a section and #{B^f} is an embedding are equivalences](fre-BABA).
}

